Url.Title: Glossary of Terms
Url.Abstract: Glossary of Terms Access Rights A user's ability to access data and use Saleslogix Network Client features. The system administrator creates a security profile for each user in Saleslogix Administrator, which determines each user's access rights within the Saleslogix Client.

Url.Title: Using the Account Assets Tab
Url.Abstract: Managing account assets in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Account Detail view, click the Assets tab. Add, edit, view, or delete an asset.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Account Details Tab
Url.Abstract: Editing or viewing additional account details in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Account Detail view, click the Details tab. Add, edit, or view additional asset details.

Url.Title: Account Detail View Contacts Tab
Url.Abstract: Managing account contacts in the Salesloigx Web Client. Open the Acount Detail view, click the Contacts tab. Add or view account's contacts.

Url.Title: Account Detail View Contracts Tab
Url.Abstract: Managing account contracts in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Account Detail view, click the Contracts tab. Verify or view account contracts.

Url.Title: Account Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Editing or viewing account information in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Account Detail view. Add, edit, or view account information.

Url.Title: Associating Accounts
Url.Abstract: Associating accounts in the Salesloigx Web Client. Use associations to identify a relationship between accounts. Open the Account Detail view, click the Associations tab. Select the associated account and describe the relationship.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - New Account Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Adding new account information in the Saleslogix Web Client.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Opportunities Tab on Account Detail view
Url.Abstract: Managing opportunities associated with an account in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Account Detail view, click the Opportunities tab.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Reseller Opportunities Tab
Url.Abstract: Managing account reseller opportunities in the Saleslogix Web Client. The Reseller Opportunities tab displays a list of the opportunities that the account is a reseller for. Open the Account Detail view, click the Opportunity Resellers tab. Add or view an account's reseller opportunites.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Activities Tab
Url.Abstract: Managing activities from the detail view Activities tab in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open a contact, account, lead, opportunity, or ticket detail view and click the Activities tab. Add, edit, view or delete an activity.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Working with the Activities List View Shortcut Menu
Url.Abstract: Using the Saleslogix Web Client Activities List view shortcut menu to view, complete or delete an activity, or open an associated contact or lead. Open the Activities List view, select one or more activities, right-click, and then select from the menu.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Using the Activity Availability Tab
Url.Abstract: Viewing the availability of the leader, other activity members, or any required resources to help you schedule your activity.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Setting Alarms
Url.Abstract: Setting activity alarms in the Saleslogix Web Client. Schedule or edit an activity, select the Alarm option and specify an alarm interval.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Alarms Tab
Url.Abstract: Managing activities with alarms in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Activities List view, click the Alarms tab. View, snooze or dismiss activity alarms.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Using Alerts
Url.Abstract: Managing activity alarms and confirmation alerts in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Alerts view from the menu bar, click the Alarms or Unconfirmed tab. Use the buttons to snooze or dismiss alarms or accept or decline unconfirmed activities.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - All Open tab
Url.Abstract: Viewing and managing open activities in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Activities List view, click the All Open tab. Use the filters to narrow the list and the common tasks or shortcut menu to schedule, edit, complete, or delete activities.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Working with Calendar Shortcut Menus
Url.Abstract: Using the Saleslogix Web Client Calendar shortcut menus to view, complete or delete an activity, open an associated contact or lead, or edit a history (completed activity) item.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - What are Activity Confirmations?
Url.Abstract: Saleslogix Activity confirmations notify you of activities that another user added you as a member or leader to an activity or when an activity that you are a member of is updated or deleted. If you are added as a member, you must confirm or decline the activity.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Confirmations Tab
Url.Abstract: You can manage all of your confirmation notifications from the Activities List view Confirmations tab, including new activities to accept or decline, deleted or changed activities, activities scheduled with you as the leader, and confirmation or declined notifications from members of an activity that you scheduled.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Recurring Activities, Daily
Url.Abstract: Scheduling activities to occur daily in the Saleslogix Web Client. If an activity occurs on a daily basis or every other day, then instead of scheduling a separate activity each time, schedule the activity to recur daily and customize the options to fit your needs.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Deleting an Event
Url.Abstract: Deleting events in the Saleslogix Web Client. If an event is cancelled or was entered in error, it should be deleted to remove it from your calendar.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Events Tab
Url.Abstract: You can manaage all of your events, or events of other Saleslogix that you have permission to view, from the Activities List view Events tab. Use the filters to narrow the list by date, user or other criteria.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Literature Tab
Url.Abstract: You can manage all of your literature requests, or requests of other Saleslogix that you have permission to view, from the Activities List view Literature tab. Use the filters to narrow the list by priority, requester or other criteria.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Recurring Activities, Monthly
Url.Abstract: Scheduling activities to occur monthly in the Saleslogix Web Client. If an activity occurs on a monthly basis, or every number of months, then instead of scheduling a separate activity each time, schedule the activity to recur monthly and customize the options to fit your needs.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - My Activities Tab
Url.Abstract: The My Activities tab in the Activities view displays all of the activities in which you are a leader or member. Use this tab to manage all of your activities.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Recurring Activities, Once
Url.Abstract: Scheduling an activity to occur only once is the default when scheduling an activity, but there are also options for scheduling daily, weekly, monthly and yearly activities.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Participants Tab
Url.Abstract: The Participants tab manages all of the contacts and leads associated with an activity when scheduling, editing, or completing an activity. you can designate a primary contact or lead, a role for each participant, and whether or not the participant was also an attendee.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Past Due Tab
Url.Abstract: View all of your past due activities on the Activities List view Past Due tab. An activity is considered past due when the scheduled start time has expired and the activity does not have an alarm.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Scheduling Recurring Activities
Url.Abstract: Scheduling activities to occur on a regular basis in the Saleslogix Web Client. Recurring activities can be scheduled to occur daily, weekly, monthly, or yearly and each choice has options that you can customize to fit your needs.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Setting Activities Options
Url.Abstract: Set activity options in the Saleslogix Web Client to customize your experience by selecting default selections and behaviors when scheduling an activity. You can set options for each activity type, for example whether a phone call has an alarm or the default duration of a to-do.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Using the Time Zone Calculator
Url.Abstract: The Time Zone Calculator shows you what time an activity will occur in a different time zone. Use the Time Zone Calculator to schedule an activity based on the time zones of all activity members.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Recurring Activities, Monthly
Url.Abstract: Scheduling activities to occur weekly in the Saleslogix Web Client. If an activity occurs on a weekly basis or every number of weeks, then instead of scheduling a separate activity each time, schedule the activity to recur weekly and customize the options to fit your needs.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Working with the Activities View
Url.Abstract: Managing activities using the Activities view in the Saleslogix Web Client. Use the tabs and filters to find the activities, alarms, confirmations, or literature requests you want to find.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Recurring Activities, Yearly
Url.Abstract: Scheduling activities to occur yearly in the Saleslogix Web Client. If an activity occurs on an annual basis, or every number of years, then instead of scheduling a separate activity each time, schedule the activity to recur yearly and customize the options to fit your needs.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Assigning Users to the Standard Role
Url.Abstract: Assigning Saleslogix users to the Standard role allows add, edit, and delete permissions to non-administrative entities such as accounts, contacts, and opportunities. Users created from the Saleslogix Web Client are assigned the standard role by default.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Creating a Secured Action
Url.Abstract: Create a Saleslogix secured action for a user interface element. Once a secured action is applied to a user interface element, only users who are assigned a role that includes the secured action can see and use the element.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Wditing or Deleting a Secured Action
Url.Abstract: Edit or delete a Saleslogix secured action. If a secured action is applied to a user interface element, only users who are assigned a role that includes the secured action can see and use the element.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Editing or Deleting a Role
Url.Abstract: Edit or delete Saleslogix user roles to change users' permissions to features and functionality in the Web Client. Users assigned to a deleted role will no longer have access to actions defined in the role.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Using the Roles List View
Url.Abstract: Using the Roles List View The Roles List view displays roles in a grid. The grid provides information about each role, such as the role name and description.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Actions tab
Url.Abstract: The Saleslogix Actions tab on the Role Detail view allows administrative users to manage the secured actions assigned to a role. The secured actions of a role determine what functionality users assigned to the role can access in the Web Client.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Role Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Editing or viewing role information in the Saleslogix Web Client. Open the Role Detail view. Add, edit, or view role information.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Users tab
Url.Abstract: The Saleslogix Users tab on the Role Detail view allows administrative users to manage the users assigned to a role. A user's access to features in the Web Client is determined by the roles they are assigned to and the secured actions of those roles.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Using the Secured Action Detail View
Url.Abstract: Use the Secured Action Detail view to edit, view or delete a secutred action.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Locations tab
Url.Abstract: The Saleslogix Locations tab on the Secured Action Detail view allows administrative users to view all of the places in nthe web Client where the secured action is applied.

Url.Title: Saleslogix Web Client Help - Roles tab
Url.Abstract: The Saleslogix Roles tab on the Secured Action Detail view allows administrative users to manage the roles to which a secured action is assigned. A user's access to features in the Web Client is determined by the roles they are assigned to and the secured actions of those roles.

Url.Title: Using the Secured Actions List View
Url.Abstract: Using the Secured Actions List View The Secured Actions List view displays secured actions in a grid. The grid provides information about each secured action, such as the secured action name and description.

Url.Title: Using the Security Manager View
Url.Abstract: Using the Security Manager View Use the Security Manager list view to manage field level access within security profiles.

Url.Title: Adding or Editing a Security Profile
Url.Abstract: Adding or Editing a Security Profile Use this dialog box to add information for a new Security Profile or edit the information for an Existing Security Profile.

Url.Title: Select a Role
Url.Abstract: Select a Role Use the Select Role dialog box to search for the role that you want to assign to the selected user(s) or secured action(s). Use the lookup to search for available roles.

Url.Title: Changing a Team's Owner
Url.Abstract: Changing a Team's Owner You can use the Teams view or Users view to change a team's owner. Teams may have multiple team owners.

Url.Title: Changing Department Members
Url.Abstract: Changing Department Members To modify department members, you can edit the department or change a user's profile.

Url.Title: Copying a Department
Url.Abstract: Copying a Department When you copy an existing department, all members are included in the new department.

Url.Title: Copying a Team
Url.Abstract: Copying a Team When you copy an existing team, all members are included in the new team. To copy Related Topics

Url.Title: Deleting a Department
Url.Abstract: Deleting a Department Before deleting a department ensure that all users are removed from the department.

Url.Title: Deleting or Renaming a Team
Url.Abstract: Deleting or Renaming a Team Use the Team Detail view to delete or rename a team. How Do I? Related Topics

Url.Title: Using the Departments List View
Url.Abstract: Using the Departments List View The Departments List view displays departments in a grid. The grid provides information about each department.

Url.Title: Department Detail View
Url.Abstract: Department Detail View Use the Detail view to see, add, or edit information for a selected record. The Detail view consists of information boxes, tabs, and a user-defined middle section.

Url.Title: Department Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Department Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes.

Url.Title: Members Tab
Url.Abstract: Members Tab The Members tab displays the users within a department. Use this tab to manage department members.

Url.Title: Teams Tab
Url.Abstract: Teams Tab The Teams tab displays the teams of which the department is a member. Use this tab to add or remove a department from a team.

Url.Title: Editing a Security Profile Within a Team
Url.Abstract: Editing a Security Profile Within a Team After you add a team member, you can modify the security rights. The initial security rights are set to match the user's default security profile. You cannot edit WebViewer security profiles. Tell me more about security...

Url.Title: Account Access Tab
Url.Abstract: Account Access Tab Use the Account Access tab to view all accounts owned by the selected team. Team members have access to the teams listed on this tab.

Url.Title: Using the Teams List View
Url.Abstract: Using the Teams List View The Teams List view displays teams in a grid. The grid provides information about each team.

Url.Title: Members Tab
Url.Abstract: Members Tab The Members tab displays the users, departments, and teams within a team. Use this tab to manage team members.

Url.Title: Team Detail View
Url.Abstract: Team Detail View Use the Detail view to see, add, or edit information for a selected record. The Detail view consists of information boxes, tabs, and a user-defined middle section.

Url.Title: Understanding Team Hierarchy
Url.Abstract: Understanding Team Hierarchy A team can consist of users, teams, and departments. When you add a user to a team, the user's immediate manager can also be included. However, there is no further inheritance (for example, the manager's manager). If you do not want the user's manager added to the team, you can clear this option on the Team Members tab.

Url.Title: Team Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Team Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes.

Url.Title: Team Owner Profile
Url.Abstract: Team Owner Profile The Team Owner Profile is the only security profile that can change ownership. Any number of team members can be team owners.

Url.Title: Associating or Disassociating with a Contact
Url.Abstract: Associating or Disassociating with a Contact If your Saleslogix implementation includes creating a contact for each Saleslogix user, you can easily associate the user and contact from the Users List view.

Url.Title: Changing a User Type
Url.Abstract: Changing a User Type Use the User Detail view to convert a user from one type to another. For example, you can change a Web Only user to a Concurrent user. You may also want to retire a user or re-activate a Retired user.

Url.Title: Copying Profile Information
Url.Abstract: Copying Profile Information You can copy configuration information from an existing user or template to one or more users. Copying profile information from one user to another overwrites existing settings. Tell me more...

Url.Title: Creating a Copy of a User
Url.Abstract: Creating a Copy of a User When you create a copy of an existing user everything is copied except user specific information such as the user name, e-mail address, and other personal information.

Url.Title: Creating a User Template
Url.Abstract: Creating a User Template User templates define the settings you want to use when creating new users. Templates are recommended because they significantly reduce administration time.

Url.Title: Managing Calendar Access Rights
Url.Abstract: Managing Calendar Access Rights Set calendar access using the following options: This can only be set up for a Remote user. However, Remote users can receive activities from both Network and Remote users.

Url.Title: Resetting Locked Out Users
Url.Abstract: Resetting Locked Out Users A user may be "locked out" from logging in to Saleslogix if the number of user's failed login attempts exceeds the number of allowed attempts. The Login Attempt Threshold is set in the Administrator on the Password tab. Resetting a locked out user changes the number of attempts to zero and allows the user to attempt to log in again.

Url.Title: Understanding Field Level Security Precedence
Url.Abstract: Understanding Field Level Security Precedence When using field level security in the Web Client, greater access takes precedence over lesser access. Access is determined by combining the maximum access of all profiles assigned to that user and owner.

Url.Title: User Profile Client System Tab
Url.Abstract: Client System Tab Use the Client System tab on the User Detail view to define a user's base templates and to set the default owner of accounts created by this user. Users can change these settings on the General tab in Options.

Url.Title: Department Membership Tab
Url.Abstract: Department Membership Tab Use the Department Membership tab on the User Detail view to add or remove the user from departments. Users can belong to more than one department.

Url.Title: User Profile Employee Tab
Url.Abstract: Employee Tab Use the Employee tab on the User Detail view to add company and personal information for a user. The Employee tab also contains user-level information that allows Saleslogix to communicate with supported third-party accounting applications.

Url.Title: User Profile Function Security Tab
Url.Abstract: Notes Tab Use the Notes tab on the User Detail view to add notes about the user. This tab allows you to add information that may not be captured on another tab.

Url.Title: Roles Tab
Url.Abstract: Roles Tab Use the Roles tab on the User Detail view to assign or remove a user from a role. When a user is assigned to a role, the user has access to the actions defined in that role. If a user is assigned to more than one role, he/she will have access to all secured actions within the roles even if each role does not contain the same actions.

Url.Title: User Profile Security Tab
Url.Abstract: Security Tab Use the Security tab on the User Detail view to define a user's default field level security profile. The system administrator always has access to everything, and the system administrator’s security access cannot be changed.

Url.Title: User Profile Service/Support Tab
Url.Abstract: Service/Support Tab Use the Service/Support tab on the User Detail view to set options related to customer service features, support features, and SpeedSearch. Consider the following when setting user access:

Url.Title: User Profile Teams Tab
Url.Abstract: Team Membership Tab Use the Team Membership tab on the User Detail view to add or remove the user from system teams. System teams group users together so that all team members have access to the same accounts.

Url.Title: User Profile Calendar Tab
Url.Abstract: User's Calendar Tab Use the User's Calendar tab on the User Detail view to set access rights for other users to view and modify this user’s calendar. By default, users do not have access to any other user’s calendars. When a user's calendar is added to another user's profile, view access rights are automatically enabled.

Url.Title: User Team Membership Tab
Url.Abstract: User Team Membership Tab User teams allow users to access accounts owned by another user. For example, if you want Lee to have access to all of Dan’s accounts, you can add Lee to Dan’s user team.

Url.Title: User Team Members Tab
Url.Abstract: User Team Members Tab User teams allow users to access accounts owned by another user. For example, if you want Lee to have access to all of Dan’s accounts, you can add Lee to Dan’s user team.

Url.Title: User Profile General Tab
Url.Abstract: User Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes.

Url.Title: Asset Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Asset Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes. Related Topics

Url.Title: Deleting an Account Asset
Url.Abstract: Deleting an Account Asset If you have the appropriate permissions, you can delete an asset. To delete Related Topics

Url.Title: Editing the Calendar Users List
Url.Abstract: Editing the Calendar Users List When using the Saleslogix calendar, with the appropriate access rights set by your system administrator, you can view and/or modify other users’ activities and events.

Url.Title: Adding Lead Sources to a Campaign
Url.Abstract: Adding Lead Sources to a Campaign You can add lead sources to a campaign using the Add Campaign Lead Source dialog box. Use the filter to narrow the list of lead sources in the Available Lead Sources tree view. You add lead sources by selecting them from the Available Lead Sources tree view and adding them to the Selected Lead Source grid. If you add a lead source in error, you can remove it.

Url.Title: Campaign Budget/Results Tab
Url.Abstract: Campaign Budget/Results Tab The Campaign Budget/Results tab helps you track campaign related costs. You can view the budget, response information, cost metrics, and opportunity statistics for the campaign. If Multi-Currency is configured, select the Display using "My Currency" check box to view budget and results information using the currency type you selected in your user options.

Url.Title: Deleting Campaign Stages
Url.Abstract: Deleting Campaign Stages Deleting a stage also deletes any tasks for that stage. To delete Related Topics

Url.Title: Deleting Campaign Tasks
Url.Abstract: Deleting Campaign Tasks You can delete tasks from a campaign stage. To delete Related Topics

Url.Title: Filtering Targets
Url.Abstract: Filtering Targets Use Include filter options to limit the target contacts and leads that display in the list. You can apply a filter by selecting the check box. The filters will retain your last selection(s) as the default values.

Url.Title: Campaign Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Campaign Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes. Related Topics

Url.Title: What are Campaigns?
Url.Abstract: What are Campaigns? A campaign is a combination of various advertising, public relations, sales promotion, and selling activities used over a period of time to achieve predetermined sales or marketing goals. A campaign can target a specific industry or group. Saleslogix Marketing allows you to track information such as the time frame of the campaign, products associated with the campaign, response rates for a campaign, and more.

Url.Title: Campaign Products Tab
Url.Abstract: Campaign Products Tab The Campaign Products tab lists all of the products associated with a campaign. You can add and remove campaign products.

Url.Title: Removing a Contact or Lead from a Campaign
Url.Abstract: Removing a Contact or Lead from a Campaign If a contact or lead does not want to be included in future campaign stages, you can remove the contact or lead from the campaign. The contact or lead is still listed as a campaign target, but the status is changed to Removed.

Url.Title: Campaign Responses Tab
Url.Abstract: Campaign Responses Tab The Campaign Responses tab lists all of the target responses for a campaign. You can add, edit, and delete campaign responses, as well as filter the list of responses.

Url.Title: Campaign Target and Response Filters
Url.Abstract: Campaign Target and Response Filters Use the Show Filters options to limit the target contacts and leads that display in the list.

Url.Title: Creating Campaign Target Groups
Url.Abstract: Creating Campaign Target Groups To manage your campaigns and campaign targets, you can create campaign target groups.

Url.Title: Campaign Targets Tab
Url.Abstract: Campaign Targets Tab The Campaign Targets tab lists all of the targets for a campaign. You can perform campaign related tasks such as, managing the target list, updating target information, exporting targets to Excel or creating a group. These features are not available if you use an external list of targets, but you can include information about the external list.

Url.Title: Updating Target Information
Url.Abstract: Updating Target Information Update multiple target contacts or leads at once using the Update Target dialog box. Use the boxes at the bottom of the dialog box to update multiple targets with the same information.

Url.Title: Campaign Opportunities Tab
Url.Abstract: Campaign Opportunities Tab The Campaign Opportunities tab lists all of the opportunities associated with a campaign.

Url.Title: Marketing Tab
Url.Abstract: Marketing Tab Use the Marketing tab on the Account, Contact or Lead Detail Views, to see the campaigns that targeted a contact or lead. You can also add or edit campaign response information, or remove a contact or lead from future stages of the campaign.

Url.Title: Setting Alerts Options
Url.Abstract: Setting Alerts Options Use the Alerts tab to set defaults to determine how you will be alerted for alarms and new unconfirmed activities.

Url.Title: Changing a Password
Url.Abstract: Changing a Password You can change your password through the Options in the Saleslogix Web Client. To change your password

Url.Title: Selecting a Time Zone
Url.Abstract: Selecting a Time Zone The Saleslogix Web Client displays your time zone in the status bar at the bottom of your browser window. The default time zone is based on your local machine's Time Zone setting. If the time zone is incorrect, you can change to another locale within the same time zone.

Url.Title: Recently Viewed
Url.Abstract: Recently Viewed Use the Recently Viewed features on the Menu Bar and Personal Workspace Welcome Tab to view a list of the records you have recently worked on.

Url.Title: Adding an Attachment
Url.Abstract: Adding an Attachment You can add an attachment to a record. All files are stored in the shared attachments directory and synchronize to and from remote databases.

Url.Title: Adding/Editing an Alternate Address
Url.Abstract: Adding/Editing an Alternate Address You can use the Address dialog box to change address information. You can have as many custom addresses as necessary for a contact or an account. However, you may select only one primary billing address and only one primary shipping address.

Url.Title: Addresses Tab
Url.Abstract: Addresses Tab The Addresses tab is located in the Account and Contact Detail views. This tab displays all addresses for the selected contact or account. Only the primary address is displayed in the Detail view.

Url.Title: Adding/Editing Response Information
Url.Abstract: Adding or Editing Response Information Use this dialog box to update response information. Responses keep track of interactions with a contact or lead. The response will appear in the Responses tabs for the Detail views.

Url.Title: Associations Tab
Url.Abstract: Associations Tab The Associations tab appears in both the Account and Contact Detail views. Associated contacts and accounts have a relationship with the selected contact or account.

Url.Title: Attachments Tab
Url.Abstract: Attachments Tab Attachments are files that are linked to a record. The Attachments tab is found on many of the detail views, including the Activity Detail view, and displays a list of attachments for the selected record.

Url.Title: Deleting an Attachment
Url.Abstract: Deleting an Attachment You can delete an attachment from a record. To delete Related Topics

Url.Title: Deleting a Response
Url.Abstract: Removing a Response Remove a response if it was entered in error or no longer applies. You can also remove a campaign response from further stages of a campaign.

Url.Title: Deleting an Alternate Address
Url.Abstract: Deleting an Alternate Address You can delete an address that is no longer valid, as long as the address is not a shipping or primary address.

Url.Title: Dragging and Dropping
Url.Abstract: Dragging and Dropping Use the drag and drop feature to rearrange portions of the Saleslogix interface. If you have installed Desktop Integration, you can also add attachments or Microsoft Outlook e-mail messages to Saleslogix.

Url.Title: Editing Attachment Information
Url.Abstract: Editing Attachment Information Use this view to alter the attachment description and upload a new version of an attachment. Attachments synchronize.

Url.Title: Adding a History Item
Url.Abstract: Adding a History Item History items are completed activities, e-mails, questions, and database changes.

Url.Title: Deleting a History Item
Url.Abstract: Deleting a History Item You can only delete a history item that you create. To delete Related Topics

Url.Title: Viewing and Editing History Items and Notes
Url.Abstract: Viewing and Editing History Items and Notes Use the History Detail View to see in-depth information about a completed activity, e-mail, literature request, note, change to the database, Visual Basic script, or question.

Url.Title: Viewing a Map for an Address
Url.Abstract: Viewing a Map for an Address This function is only available for the first line of the primary address of an account, contact or lead. The second address line is not used. If the pound (#) sign appears in an address, place it on the second address line to allow MapQuest to better locate the address.

Url.Title: More Tabs
Url.Abstract: More Tabs Use More Tabs to open additional tab views. More Tabs may display on any of the Detail views. You can drag and drop tabs to and from the More Tabs section.

Url.Title: Adding a Note
Url.Abstract: Adding a Note You use notes to document the outcome of an activity and to record interactions with an account, contact, lead, or opportunity. The notes you add appear in the Notes/History tab on the Account, Contact, Lead, and Opportunity Detail views.

Url.Title: Deleting a Note
Url.Abstract: Deleting a Note You can only delete notes that you create. You must delete the entire history item associated with the note.

Url.Title: Notes/History Tab
Url.Abstract: The Notes/History Tab displays on the Account, Contact, Opportunity and Lead Detail views. The tab contains filtering options that allow you to quickly access important information. You can also use this tab to e-mail a history record, create a Microsoft Word document, view an attachment, or edit notes.

Url.Title: Campaign Responses Tab
Url.Abstract: Responses Tab Use the Responses tab on the Account, Contact or Lead Detail Views to see contact and lead responses. Responses keep track of interactions with a contact or lead. You can also add or edit response information.

Url.Title: Using the Returns Tab
Url.Abstract: Using the Returns Tab The Returns tab on the Account and Ticket Detail views lists all returns for the selected record.

Url.Title: Integration Sync History Tab
Url.Abstract: Integration Sync History Tab The Integration Sync History tab is available from the Contact and Lead Detail view only if the contact or lead is synchronized with an external integration. The Integration Sync History tab lists each time the record was synchronized between Saleslogix and the external integration.

Url.Title: Tickets Tab
Url.Abstract: Tickets Tab The Tickets tab on the Contact and Account Detail views lists all tickets reported by the contact or account. You can use the Tickets tab to open the detail view of a selected ticket, or to add a new ticket.

Url.Title: Timeline
Url.Abstract: Timeline A Timeline shows the occurrence and duration of events, such as activities, history, tickets and opportunities over a period of time (past, present, and future).

Url.Title: Changing the Status of a Contact Process
Url.Abstract: Changing the Status of a Contact Process The Web Client allows you to suspend or abort a process, and to restart a suspended process. Aborted processes are permanently ended.

Url.Title: Lead Source Detail View
Url.Abstract: Every contact has a lead source, such as a magazine ad, trade show, and so on that generates sales leads. This dialog box displays the description, creation date, abbreviation, source date, type, and status of the lead source associated with the current contact.

Url.Title: Adding New Contact for Existing Account
Url.Abstract: Adding New Contact for Existing Account Use the Insert Contact/Account view to add a new contact anexisting account. The account boxes will be populated with the existing account's information and cannot be edited.

Url.Title: Adding New Contact and Account
Url.Abstract: Adding a New Contact and Account To add Related Topics

Url.Title: Associating Contacts
Url.Abstract: Use associations to create relationships between contacts. Associations are listed on the Associations tab on the Contacts Detail view. More than one contact association might exist for a particular contact.

Url.Title: Associating or Disassociating with a User
Url.Abstract: Associating or Disassociating with a User If your Saleslogix implementation includes creating a contact for each Saleslogix user, you can easily associate the user and contact from the Contacts List view.

Url.Title: Duplicating a Contact
Url.Abstract: Duplicating a Contact You can duplicate a contact for another account. This is useful if a contact joins another company and you want to associate the contact with both accounts. If you want to associate the contact with only the new account you can move the contact to that account.

Url.Title: Contact Details Tab
Url.Abstract: Contact Details Tab The Details Tab appears in the Contact Detail view. This tab contains specific information about the contact, such as the local time and time zone where the contact is located, who the contact was referred by, the department in which the contact works, the salutation, and the contact's assistant's name. You can edit the information at any time by clicking in a box and typing new information, or selecting from a list of available items.

Url.Title: Contact Detail View Web Access Tab
Url.Abstract: Contact Detail View Web Access Tab The Contact Detail Web Access tab is available to administrative users or users who have been given permission to grant access to contacts for Saleslogix Customer Portal. When contacts are granted access, they can log on to Saleslogix Customer Portal, view all tickets in their account, add new tickets, change ticket status, and close tickets. Customers can view or add information on tickets for their accounts only. Customers can view or add information on tickets for their accounts only.

Url.Title: Contact Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Contact Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes. Related Topics

Url.Title: Copying Information to Clipboard
Url.Abstract: Copying Information to the Clipboard The information is copied to the Clipboard, so that you can use it in other applications. This is useful if you need to copy information into an e-mail, or Microsoft Word document.

Url.Title: Lead Sources Tab
Url.Abstract: Lead Sources Tab The Lead Sources tab appears in the Contact Detail view. Each time you add a new contact or opportunity, you can associate a lead source to indicate how your company found out about the contact or opportunity (trade shows, magazine ads, telesales, and so forth). Click a lead source to view detailed information about it. Columns on the tab include: date, description, and source code.

Url.Title: What Happens When I Move or Duplicate a Contact?
Url.Abstract: What Happens When I Move or Duplicate a Contact? You can move a contact or make a duplicate of a contact and attach it to another account.

Url.Title: New Contact Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Contact Information Boxes The contact information boxes contain in-depth information about the selected contact. You can add, edit or delete the information as needed.

Url.Title: Opportunities Tab - Contact Detail view
Url.Abstract: Opportunities Tab - Contact Detail view You can use the Opportunities tab of the Contact Detail view to see information about opportunities linked to the selected contact. You can also associate the contact with an opportunity.

Url.Title: Potential Matching Records
Url.Abstract: Potential Matching Records When adding a contact or account, you can compare the contact or account you are adding to contacts or accounts that exist in the database. If a record exists in the database with the same information, you can avoid having duplicate records. If you choose to use a matching account, the account information will be added to the account boxes in the Contact/Account Information dialog box. If the contact or account information does not match, you can continue adding your contact or account.

Url.Title: Setting a Primary Contact
Url.Abstract: Setting a Primary Contact A primary contact is the main contact for an account or opportunity. Typically, the primary contact is the person in an organization that you contact most often.

Url.Title: Processes Tab
Url.Abstract: Processes Tab The Processes tab appears in the Contact Detail view. Use the Processes tab to manage contact processes attached to a single contact.

Url.Title: Selecting an Address
Url.Abstract: Selecting an Alternate Address You can use the Select an Address dialog box to select an existing address for a new contact. The Select another Address button is available only if existing addresses are available. For example, if you are adding a contact to an account with multiple addresses, the account's addresses are available.

Url.Title: Copying a Contract
Url.Abstract: Copying a Contract You can copy information from an existing contract to create a new one. If you use the Copy button, Saleslogix copies information from the original record.

Url.Title: Deleting a Contract
Url.Abstract: Deleting a Contract If you have the appropriate permissions, no tickets are associated with the contract, and the contract is not active, you can delete an unused contract for an account.

Url.Title: Editing a Contract
Url.Abstract: Editing a Contract Use the Contract Detail view to edit information for an active or inactive contract. To undo any changes, click Reset before clicking the Save button.

Url.Title: Contract Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Contract Information Boxes Related Topics

Url.Title: Contract Reference Number Duplicate
Url.Abstract: Contract Reference Number Duplicate Contract Reference Numbers must be unique. If a reference number already exists, the Contract Reference # Duplicate dialog box opens.

Url.Title: Contract Tickets Tab
Url.Abstract: Contract Tickets Tab The Tickets tab displays all tickets associated to the contract. To open Related Topics

Url.Title: Contract Covered Assets Tab
Url.Abstract: Covered Assets Tab The Covered Assets tab displays information for each asset that is covered by the contract. You can use this tab to associate and disassociate assets covered by the contract.

Url.Title: Selecting a Contract
Url.Abstract: Selecting a Contract You can use the Select Contract view when the account has more than one service contract and you need to select the appropriate contract to charge the ticket against.

Url.Title: Promoting a Group to the Dashboard
Url.Abstract: Promoting a Group to the Dashboard Promoting a group to the Dashboard sends all the group data to a group list widget on the dashboard.

Url.Title: Adding a Defect Resolution
Url.Abstract: Adding a Defect Resolution When you determine how a defect is going to be resolved, you need to add the information to the defect.

Url.Title: Changing the Status of a Defect
Url.Abstract: Changing the Status of a Defect When a defect is created, the status is set to Open. However, your organization may use other status types to indicate different stages in the defect resolution process. Consult your system administrator for more information on the status types your company uses.

Url.Title: Copying a Defect
Url.Abstract: Copying a Defect You can copy information from an existing defect to create a new one. If you use the Copy button, Saleslogix copies information from the original record.

Url.Title: Deleting a Defect
Url.Abstract: Deleting a Defect If you have the appropriate privileges, you can delete a defect. To delete Related Topics

Url.Title: Defect Details Tab
Url.Abstract: Defect Details Tab The Details Tab appears in the Defect Detail view. This tab contains specific information about the defect.

Url.Title: Editing a Defect
Url.Abstract: Editing a Defect Use the Defect Detail view to edit information for an existing defect. For example, you can update the status, change the assignment to another person, or enter the details of how a defect was resolved.

Url.Title: Adding or Editing Defect Tasks
Url.Abstract: Adding or Editing Defect Tasks Use the Defect Task information boxes to add details for a new activity and to edit an existing activity.

Url.Title: Defect Tasks Tab
Url.Abstract: Using the Defect Tasks Tab Use this tab to see all activities associated with the defect, to add or change time for working on a defect, or edit an activity. Activities can be any action involved in processing or resolving the defect. For example, if you need to research for the defect, add this activity here.

Url.Title: Defect Tickets Tab
Url.Abstract: Using the Defect Tickets Tab Use this tab to add or remove an association between tickets and defects. Management and other users may use this information to determine the severity of the defect and actions needed to correct the defect.

Url.Title: Tracking a Defect
Url.Abstract: Tracking a Defect Tracking a defect means you are working to resolve the defect. Use the following questions or refer to your company policies for the business rules for tracking defects in your organization.

Url.Title: Defect Audit Trail Tab
Url.Abstract: Using the Defect Audit Trail Tab The Defect Audit Trail tab contains a historical log of actions, such as changes made to fields on the Defect Detail view. The system automatically posts some of the information in the Audit Trail boxes on the tab; users cannot change that information. A customer service user or manager can use the Audit Trail tab to track and measure defect response time and effort.

Url.Title: Using the Comments Tab
Url.Abstract: Using the Comments Tab Use this tab for all internal notes related to a defect or contract. To add Related Topics

Url.Title: Defect Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Defect Information Boxes The following table describes the default information boxes. Related Topics

Url.Title: Defect Returns Tab
Url.Abstract: Using the Defect Returns Tab Use this tab to add or remove an association between returns and defects. Management and other users may use this information to determine the severity of the defect and actions needed to correct the defect.

Url.Title: Access Rights
Url.Abstract: Access Rights Access rights determine your ability to use features located on menus, toolbars and the Navigation Bar. Your access rights also determine the data you can access and are defined in the Administrator by the Saleslogix system administrator.

Url.Title: Customizing Your List View Groups
Url.Abstract: Customizing Your List View Groups You can customize your list view tabs by adding or removing columns, changing the column order and adjusting the column widths. Saleslogix will remember these changes each time you log in using the same browser and computer. You can also hide or show the list view check boxes.

Url.Title: Installing and Using Saleslogix Desktop Integration
Url.Abstract: Installing and Using Saleslogix Desktop Integration The Saleslogix Desktop Integration Module is a collection of features to enhance your Saleslogix Web experience.

Url.Title: E-mailing Contacts or Leads
Url.Abstract: E-mailing Contacts or Leads This function is only available if your e-mail program is compatible with your browser, and an e-mail address has been entered into the database for a contact or lead. If you enter an e-mail address for a contact or lead, update the record to enter the address in the database before attempting to send e-mail.

Url.Title: Exporting Records to a File
Url.Abstract: Exporting Records to a File You can export records to a file. The group column headings and formatting will also be exported.

Url.Title: Working with Grids in List Views and Tabs
Url.Abstract: Working with Grids in List Views and Tabs There are features that allow you to change the way information is displayed in a grid. You can use these features to sort records or to hide or rearrange columns in the grid.

Url.Title: Linking Addresses
Url.Abstract: Linking Addresses Use the Link Addresses step to determine what address information will be included when merging records.

Url.Title: Linking Contact Addresses
Url.Abstract: Linking Contact Addresses The Link Contact Addresses step allows you to associate the contacts you linked in the previous screen with address information while merging records.

Url.Title: Using a Memo Box
Url.Abstract: Using a Memo Box Use a memo box to add additional information, including notes, comments or a description.

Url.Title: Merging Records
Url.Abstract: Merging Records Use merge records to eliminate duplicates in your database. You can only merge duplicates to which you have access rights.

Url.Title: Working with the Navigation Bar Shortcut Menus
Url.Abstract: Working with the Navigation Bar Shortcut Menus The Navigation Bar shortcut menus enable you to open a list view, create a new record, or when applicable, create a new group. The shortcut menu options available vary depending on the record type.

Url.Title: Performing Process Tasks
Url.Abstract: Performing Process Tasks If you have configured process orchestration you can perform Process Tasks from the Common Tasks area in the Task Pane in some list views.

Url.Title: Unsaved Data Reminders
Url.Abstract: Unsaved Data Reminders When you update record information, an "*unsaved data" reminder appears in the Title Bar. If you have unsaved data and try to browse to another page, you will be prompted to save your changes. Click OK to save your changes or Cancel to remain on the page.

Url.Title: Sample Help Topic
Url.Abstract: Sample Help Topic This is a sample help topic. Replace the text in this topic with the instructions for using your custom view, then save the topic using the suggested naming convention.

Url.Title: Using the Summary View
Url.Abstract: Using the Summary View Use the Summary view to see commonly used information for each record type. The information and available features depend on the record type.

Url.Title: Supported Desktop Integtration Features By Browser
Url.Abstract: Supported Desktop Integtration Features By Browser The Saleslogix Desktop Integration Module is a collection of features to enhance your Saleslogix Web experience. Some browsers support features, but require Desktop Integration and other features are only supported on certain browsers. See the following table for details:

Url.Title: Using the Task Pane
Url.Abstract: Using the Task Pane The Task Pane consists of common tasks and features designed to help you complete your work. The available options depend on the record type and type of view where you are working.

Url.Title: Using Task Pane Filters
Url.Abstract: Using Task Pane Filters Use the Task Pane Filters to narrow the list of records that display in a list view group. The available filters are based on the columns in the selected list view and the information contained in those columns. Filters are saved on your computer until your browser cache is cleared.

Url.Title: Adding or Removing Filters
Url.Abstract: Adding or Removing Filters Filters allow you to narrow the list of records that display in a list view. The available filters are based on the columns in the selected list view and the information contained in those columns. However, you can customize the list of filters to only include the filters that you use for each group.

Url.Title: Adding or Removing Filter Items
Url.Abstract: Adding or Removing Filter Items Filters allow you to narrow the list of records that display in a list view. You can customize your filters to only include the filter items you want to use for each group.

Url.Title: Using the Detail View Group List
Url.Abstract: Using the Detail View Group List The detail view Group List displays a list of all of the records in a group or lookup from within the detail view. You can see at a glance other records that are in the group or lookup, or click a record in the list to navigate to that record's detail view. There are two different modes for the Group List, the regular mode displays only the record name, the extended mode displays additional columns with more information. You can set options to determine the default behavior for the Group List.

Url.Title: Edit Name Information
Url.Abstract: Adding or Editing Name Information Use the Edit Name dialog box to add or edit name information.This ensures that a name includes a first and last name and that the name is stored correctly in the database. The templates and mail merge features require the correct name, title and suffix.

Url.Title: General Options
Url.Abstract: General Options To set general options Related Topics

Url.Title: Understanding the Available Buttons
Url.Abstract: Understanding the Available Buttons Many features in the Saleslogix Web Client are accessed through buttons. The following list shows each of the buttons available, and describes the action each button performs. When you drag your mouse across a button in the Saleslogix Web Client, a tool tip explaining the button function appears. Buttons are referred to by their tool tip.

Url.Title: Adding or Removing Ad Hoc Group Records
Url.Abstract: Adding or Removing Ad Hoc Group Records You can manage your ad hoc groups by adding or removing records.

Url.Title: Copying a Group
Url.Abstract: Copying a Group You can select an existing group and copy it. You can maintain the existing conditions of the group or modify the conditions to suit your needs. You cannot copy ad hoc groups.

Url.Title: Setting a Default Group
Url.Abstract: Setting a Default Group You can set a default group for each list view. The default group is the group that will be open when you first go to the list view. The default group also determines the layout of new groups. There can only be one default group per list view.

Url.Title: Deleting Groups
Url.Abstract: Deleting Groups You can delete a group that you are no longer using. You can only delete groups you added. However, the system administrator can delete all groups.

Url.Title: Using the Group Shortcut Menu
Url.Abstract: Using the Group Shortcut Menu The groups shortcut menu enables you to create and manage groups. To open the groups shortcut menu

Url.Title: Group Manager
Url.Abstract: Group Manager Use the Groups list to view and manage all of your groups for a list or detail view. You can search, show hidden groups and hide groups. You can also add a new group.

Url.Title: Hiding Groups
Url.Abstract: Hiding Groups You can hide a group that you no longer want to view, but do not want to delete. To hide a group

Url.Title: Group Options
Url.Abstract: Group Options Use the Groups options tab to determine how your groups, list views and lookups will appear and behave. These options only apply when the current user is logged in to the Saleslogix Web Client.

Url.Title: Sharing Groups with Other Users
Url.Abstract: Sharing Groups with Other Users You can share your groups with other Saleslogix users, teams, or departments.

Url.Title: Showing Hidden Groups
Url.Abstract: Showing Hidden Groups You can show a group that has been hidden. To show a hidden group Related Topics

Url.Abstract: Troubleshooting Integrations - Cannot Start the Saleslogix SData Sync Service You may encounter the following issues when synchronizing information between Saleslogix and supported integrations.

Url.Title: Accounting Tasks Pane
Url.Abstract: Accounting Tasks Pane This feature is only available if your administrator has configured Accounting Integration.

Url.Title: Account Detail View Accounting Details Tab
Url.Abstract: Account Detail View Accounting Details Tab (Accounting Integration Only) The Accounting Details tab displays additional company information from the integrated accounting application. This information synchronizes to the linked account in the accounting system.

Url.Title: Accounting Sales Orders Tab
Url.Abstract: Accounting Sales Orders Tab (Accounting Integration Only) The Accounting Sales Orders tab in the Account Detail view displays the account's sales orders from the integrated accounting system. You can use this tab to see information such as the order date, status, charges, and so on. This information is read-only.

Url.Title: Accounting Tab
Url.Abstract: Accounting Tab (Accounting Integration Only) The Accounting tab in the Account Detail view displays link information for accounting systems currently integrated with Saleslogix. You can use this tab to manage the links between systems. Only accounting systems configured in the Integration Detail View appear in the list. This view contains the following columns:

Url.Title: Running the SLXConversion Utility
Url.Abstract: Running the SLXConversion Utility Before setting up your Accounting Integration endpoints, you must run the SLXConversion utility to update Account Phone Number and E-mail records. This utility supports integration by adding columns to the Saleslogix database to enable a 1:many relationship for phone numbers and email addresses in Accounts and Contacts.

Url.Title: Invoices Tab
Url.Abstract: Invoices Tab (Accounting Integration Only) The Invoices tab in the Account Detail view displays the account's invoices from the integrated accounting system. You can use this tab to see information such as the invoice status, balance, amount, and so on. This information is read-only.

Url.Title: Customer Payments Tab
Url.Abstract: Customer Payments Tab (Accounting Integration Only) The Customer Payments tab in the Account Detail view displays the payment status of the account's invoices. This information is read-only.

Url.Title: Creating a New Account from a Sales Order
Url.Abstract: Creating a New Account from a Sales Order You can create a sales order before you create an account or contact. If the prospect decides to do business with your company, you can create a new account and contact from the sales order with limited company and contact information.

Url.Title: Invoice Detail View
Url.Abstract: Invoice Detail View The Invoice Detail view displays read-only information from your accounting system.

Url.Title: Merge Contacts
Url.Abstract: Merge Contacts The Merge Contacts screen displays contacts that you are either merging in Saleslogix or linking an account you are to the customer you selected in an accounting system. Use this screen to create links and merge your contacts within Saleslogix or between Saleslogix and integrated accounting system contact records.

Url.Title: Merge Data
Url.Abstract: Merge Data The Merge Data screen displays differences in data when you are linking records between Saleslogix and an accounting system. Use this screen to select the data you want to use when merging records. The data you keep overwrites the data in the other system. Tell me more...

Url.Title: Payment Detail View
Url.Abstract: Payment Detail View The Payment Detail view displays read-only information from your accounting system.

Url.Title: Sales Order Detail View (Accounting Integration)
Url.Abstract: Sales Order Detail View (Accounting Integration) (Accounting Integration Only) The Sales Order Detail view displays read-only information from your accounting system.

Url.Title: Search for Matches
Url.Abstract: Search for Matches The Search for Matches screen allows you to select the criteria to use when searching the accounting system for customers that are potential matches for the account you are linking from Saleslogix.

Url.Title: Select an Accounting System
Url.Abstract: Select an Accounting System The Select an Accounting System screen in the Link to Accounting wizard displays the accounting systems available to link with the selected account.

Url.Title: Select or Create Account
Url.Abstract: Select or Create Account The Select or Create Account screen displays the customer(s) in the accounting system that are a potential match for the account you are linking in Saleslogix. You can choose an existing customer to link, create a new customer record, or refine your search criteria and search again.

Url.Title: Authorizing Services
Url.Abstract: Authorizing Services Use the Authorize Services options tab to authorize a connection with an external service. Before you can authorize a service, your administrator must configure the integration and grant access to users. These options only apply when the current user is logged in to the Saleslogix Web Client.

Url.Title: Changing the Ad Hoc Contact Group
Url.Abstract: Changing the Contact Sync Group

Url.Title: Configuring the Contact Sync Group
Url.Abstract: Configuring the Contact Sync Group To synchronize contact information between Saleslogix and Outlook, you must designate the group as the contact sync group. If the group does not already exist, then you must first create the contact sync group.

Url.Title: Integration Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Integration Information Boxes The integration information boxes contain information about the selected integration. Depending on the integration, you can view or edit the information as needed. Some information may not be edited.

Url.Title: Adding or Editing a Basic Integration Link
Url.Abstract: Adding or Editing a Basic Integration Link Use the Add or Edit Link dialog box to add or edit integration links. If an integration's authorization type is Basic, use this dialog box to add links.

Url.Title: Managing Schema
Url.Abstract: Managing Schema Use the Manage Schema dialog to compare the database schema in Saleslogix with your integration schema to ensure data integrity. You can compare data for various resources to determine if differences in string lengths exist between systems.

Url.Title: Integrations Options Tab
Url.Abstract: Integrations Options Tab Use the Options tab to view and edit options that are specific to an integration. These options determine what and how information is synchronized between the integration and Saleslogix.

Url.Title: Integrations Resources Tab
Url.Abstract: Integrations Resources Tab Use the Resources tab to view integration-specific resource definitions and behavior. Resources define what information is mapped between Saleslogix and the integration contract. From this tab you can see whether a resource is enabled to synchronize for the integration and in what direction information is synchronized.

Url.Title: Integrations Scopes Tab
Url.Abstract: Integrations Scopes Tab Use the Scopes tab to view the scopes that are defined for an integration. Scopes determine what information is available from the integration to Saleslogix.

Url.Title: Log Items Tab
Url.Abstract: Log Items Tab The Log Items tab displays the messages generated when a synchronization job is processed. Use the filters on this tab to define the logging information you want to view.

Url.Title: Matching Records Between Saleslogix and Outlook
Url.Abstract: Matching Records Between Saleslogix and Outlook To avoid duplicate records and find matching records in either application, Saleslogix searches for matching records based on the following key fields:

Url.Title: Matching Tab
Url.Abstract: Matching Tab Use the Matching tab to configure the options for finding matches between Saleslogix and any integrated accounting systems. The options you select here define how the data entered by users in Saleslogix will be matched to existing data in your accounting system. Tell me more...

Url.Title: SData Sync Configuration View Integrations Tab
Url.Abstract: SData Sync Configuration View Integrations Tab Use the Integrations tab to see a list of integrations that synchronize data through SData. You can also enable or disable synchronization for an integration or manually synchronize all of the integrations at once.

Url.Title: Sync History Detail View
Url.Abstract: Sync History Detail View Use the Sync History Detail view to see detailed information about a synchronization history item. Synchronization history items are associated with jobs run between Saleslogix and an external integration. Sync history information shows what records were synchronized and when they were synchronized and can provide information for troubleshooting synchronization problems.

Url.Title: Sync Job Detail View
Url.Abstract: Sync Job Detail View Use the Detail view to see, add, or edit information for a selected record. The Detail view consists of information boxes, tabs, and a user-defined middle section.

Url.Title: Sync Job Sync History Tab
Url.Abstract: Sync Job Sync History Tab The Sync History tab on the Sync Job Detail view lists each synchronization history record that is associated with a sync job.

Url.Title: Understanding Email Integration
Url.Abstract: Understanding Email Integration The e-mail integration features provide the ability to send e-mail messages from Saleslogix using Outlook or to send e-mail messages from Outlook to one or more Saleslogix contacts or leads and record them as Saleslogix history items.

Url.Title: Users Integrations Tab
Url.Abstract: Users Integrations Tab Use the Integrations tab to view all of the integrations associated with the user.

Url.Title: Definitions
Url.Abstract: Definitions The Definitions tab contains a list of pre-defined job types. Select a job type from those listed and use the schedule wizard to set a time and recurrence for running the job.

Url.Title: Creating and Modifying Schedules
Url.Abstract: Using the Run/Schedule Job Dialog Box The Run/Schedule Job dialog box enables you to set labels and parameters for the job type you are scheduling. The options available may vary depending on the job selected and the location from which you opened the dialog box.

Url.Title: Scheduling and Editing Job Schedules
Url.Abstract: Editing Job Schedules The Schedules tab lists all jobs that have been set to run at a scheduled time and provides information about that schedule. From this tab, you can delete or modify a job schedule.

Url.Title: Viewing the Progress of a Job
Url.Abstract: Viewing the Progress of a Job The Executions tab shows jobs that are in process. In addition to the job name, you can see the user who started the job, the phase the job has reached, whether has completed successfully, and the path where the completed file is stored. If there job has failed to execute correctly, an error message is visible in the Execution Result column.

Url.Title: Changing the Lead Owner
Url.Abstract: You can use the Update Multiple Leads dialog box to change the owner or account manager for multiple leads at once.

Url.Title: Converting Leads
Url.Abstract: Converting Leads Once lead information has been qualified, a lead can be converted to a contact and account. The Convert Lead dialog box displays any contacts or accounts with matching information. Leads with matching information can be merged with an existing contact, added to an existing account, or the lead can be added as a new contact and account. You can change the filter criteria used to find matching records.

Url.Title: Editing Leads
Url.Abstract: Editing a Lead Use the Lead Detail view to edit lead information. To edit Related Topics

Url.Title: Defining a Delimiter
Url.Abstract: Use this view to select the appropriate delimiter value for your list and preview records before you import them to Saleslogix. A delimiter parses fields in a list. Saleslogix analyzes the list to determine which delimiter is currently used, but you can select a different delimiter if necessary.

Url.Title: Import Leads - Testing for Duplicate Records
Url.Abstract: Import Leads - Testing for Duplicate Records Use this view to preview the number of potential duplicates and errors before you import a list of leads. If you have a large number of potential duplicates, adjust your match filters so that only duplicate records are found.

Url.Title: Resolving Duplicate Leads
Url.Abstract: Resolving Duplicate Leads Found During Import When importing leads, you can look for other leads or contacts that exist in the database. Use this view to manually import or merge the duplicate records.

Url.Title: Lead Import Activity Information Boxes
Url.Abstract: Lead Import Activity Information Boxes Use this view to add an activity to each imported lead. The full text of the activity, date and time appears in the Activities tabs for the Detail views.

Url.Title: Using Advanced Match Options
Url.Abstract: Using Advanced Match Options Use advanced match options to define how potential matches are found. To set advanced options

Url.Title: Managing Duplicate Records
Url.Abstract: Managing Duplicate Records When importing leads, you can look for other leads or contacts that exist in the database. If a record exists in the database with the same information, you can avoid having duplicate records.

Url.Title: Selecting a File to Import
Url.Abstract: Selecting a File to Import Use this view to select the file that contains the leads you want to import.

Url.Title: Selecting Import Group Actions
Url.Abstract: Selecting Import Group Actions Use this view to specify actions to be performed for the leads you import to Saleslogix. You can add a note, add the record to a campaign, create a response or schedule an activity.

Url.Title: Lead Import History - Duplicates Tab
Url.Abstract: Lead Import History - Duplicates Tab Use this tab to view a list of records marked as a duplicates that must be resolved before it can be imported.

Url.Title: Lead Import History - History Tab
Url.Abstract: Lead Import History - History Tab Use this tab to view a list of records that encountered problems during the import. Records display in the tab if any of the following conditions occurred:

Url.Title: Using the Lead Import History List View
Url.Abstract: Using the Lead Import History List View Use the Import History List view to see a list of imported lead lists.

Url.Title: Mapping Import Fields
Url.Abstract: Mapping Import Fields Use this view to map fields in the import list to fields in Saleslogix. You can save import information, such as matching fields, default lead owner and default lead source, and use it for future imports.

Url.Title: Adding an Import Group Action Note
Url.Abstract: Adding an Import Group Action Note Use this view to add a note to each imported lead. The full text of the note, date and time appear in the Notes tabs for the Detail views.

Url.Title: Processing the Import
Url.Abstract: Processing the Import Use this view to monitor the progress of the import. To cancel the import To view the import history

Url.Title: Adding an Import Group Action Response
Url.Abstract: Adding an Import Group Action Response Use this view to add a response to each imported lead. Responses keep track of interactions with a contact or lead. The response will appear on the Responses tabs in the Detail views.

Url.Title: Reviewing Import Selections
Url.Abstract: Reviewing Import Selections Use this view to review your selections before you import leads to Saleslogix.

Url.Title: Adding an Import Group Action Campaign Target
Url.Abstract: Adding an Import Group Action Campaign Target Use this view to add each imported lead as a campaign target. Each lead will appear on the selected Campaign Detail view Targets tab.

Url.Title: Merging Duplicate Records
Url.Abstract: Merging Duplicate Records When converting a lead or resolving a duplicate import record you can merge the two duplicate records.

Url.Title: Rules for Automatically Merging Records During Import
Url.Abstract: Rules for Automatically Merging Records During Import During a lead import you have the option to automatically merge duplicate records that are found using the match filters you select. Url.Title: Lead Details Tab
Url.Abstract: Lead Details Tab The Details tab appears in the Lead Detail view. This tab contains specific information about the lead. You can edit the information at any time by clicking in a box and typing new information, or selecting from a list of available items.

Url.Abstract: Looking for Matching Lead Records You can compare the lead to other leads, contacts or accounts that exist in the database. If a record exists in the database with the same information, you can avoid having duplicate records.

Url.Title: Saving an Import Template
Url.Abstract: Saving an Import Template You can save import information, such as matching fields, default lead owner and default lead source, and use it for future imports.

Url.Title: Adding, Renaming, or Deleting a Library Folder
Url.Abstract: Adding, Renaming, or Deleting a Library Folder For better organization, you can use Library folders to group documents together.

Url.Title: Library Document Properties
Url.Abstract: Library Document Properties Use the Document Properties dialog box to add to or change the properties of files in the Library. In addition to the editable fields, this dialog box provides the following read-only information:

Url.Title: Library
Url.Abstract: Working with the Library The Library is a central repository for company information (in the form of documents, URLs, and so on) that provides an easy way to distribute information to remote users. Files are organized into folders and sorted by name. Click the column headings to sort the library files list.

Url.Title: Adding a Literature Item
Url.Abstract: Adding a Literature Item You can add documents to the list of available literature. This list is available when scheduling a literature request. You can also edit information about existing documents, such as the quantity on hand.

Url.Title: Deleting Literature from the List
Url.Abstract: Deleting Literature from the List You can delete a literature item. Deleting a literature item deletes it from the list of available items when creating a literature request, but does not delete the item from literature requests that have already been scheduled.

Url.Title: Literature Item Detail View
Url.Abstract: Literature Item Detail View Use the Detail view to see, add or edit information for a selected record.

Url.Title: Editing a Literature Item
Url.Abstract: Editing a Literature Item Use the Literature Item Detail view to edit literature item information. To edit
